               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183209060156"></xptr>RICHARD SILVER. I am a <rs id="t18320906-375-viclabel2123" type="occupation">silk-weaver</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-375-victim3086 t18320906-375-viclabel2123"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18320906-375-crimeloc2124">Hare-street, Bethnal-green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-375-crimeloc2124" type="placeName" value="Hare-street, Bethnal-green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-375-crimeloc2124" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-375-off2121 t18320906-375-crimeloc2124"></join>; the prisoner was sent from Bethnal-green workhouse to nurse my wife in her confinement. On Sunday, the 12th of August, when I came home to dine, there was no dinner cooked, and she had left my wife in bed unable to help herself - I missed these things; she came again on Monday; I said, "Where are the things you have taken away, belonging to the Benevolent Society-box? tell me, or you will get me into disgrace;" she then told me, and I found them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-375-person3087">
                  SARAH 
                  BAILEY
               <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3087" type="surname" value="BAILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3087" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3087" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a clothes-shop near Bethnalgreen. The prisoner brought me a bed-gown, five napkins, and a jacket; I gave her 1s. 3d. for them - they are very old; I did not observe the society's stamp on them till it was shown to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-375-person3088">
                  JOHN 
                  CARPENTER
               <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3088" type="surname" value="CARPENTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3088" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-375-person3088" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I have the property; some of it is very old.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. His wife asked me to go and pawn something belonging to the box - I refused; she sent her boy to pawn them - the following week she asked me again, and I pawned some for 3s.; I was taken ill, and asked this woman to lend me 1s. 3d. on these things - I was to return it again; I told his wife what I had done - she said I was welcome.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18320906-375-verdict2125" type="verdictDescription">
